---
const symptoms = [
  'A critical invoice slips past its due date.',
  'A lease renewal falls through the cracks.',
  'A lead gets dropped because nobody copy-pasted from one sheet to another.',
  'Slack lights up at 11 p.m. asking what the latest version actually is.',
  'A new hire spends week one untangling tribal knowledge.'
];
---
<section id="diagnosis" class="relative bg-carbon py-24 md:py-36 border-t border-cobalt-500/30 overflow-hidden">
  {/* Cobalt accent stripe top-left */}
  <div aria-hidden="true" class="absolute top-0 left-0 h-1 w-32 bg-cobalt-500"></div>

  <div class="container">
    {/* Kicker + headline */}
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-6 items-end">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3 meta-strip text-cobalt-400 border-t border-cobalt-500/40 pt-4">
        Diagnosis
      </div>
      <h2 class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9 font-display text-display-xl tracking-tightest text-balance">
        Your operation is scaling.<br/>
        Your infrastructure is <span class="text-cobalt-400">fragile</span>.
      </h2>
    </div>

    {/* Body + symptoms list */}
    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-24 grid grid-cols-12 gap-x-6 gap-y-12 items-start">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-6 space-y-6 text-ash-300 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-pretty">
          You&rsquo;ve built a successful business through sheer force of will. The backend is
          a chaotic web of isolated tools, frantic Slack messages, and manual data entry held
          together by the people who&rsquo;ve been there longest.
        </p>
        <p class="text-pretty">
          You lie awake wondering whether something slipped through the cracks &mdash; an
          invoice, a renewal, a lead, an onboarding step. The next morning you go fix it,
          and on a long enough timeline, that&rsquo;s the work.
        </p>
        <p class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl tracking-tight text-white text-balance pt-2">
          You don&rsquo;t have an operations problem.<br class="hidden sm:block"/>
          You have an architecture problem.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Symptoms spec card */}
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 md:col-start-8 border border-white/10 bg-carbon-800">
        <div class="px-6 sm:px-8 py-5 border-b border-white/10 flex items-center justify-between meta-strip">
          <span class="text-ash-300">Common symptoms</span>
          <span class="text-cobalt-400">File 02.01</span>
        </div>
        <ul class="divide-y divide-white/10">
          {symptoms.map((s, i) => (
            <li class="grid grid-cols-[3rem_1fr] gap-3 items-start px-6 sm:px-8 py-4 text-sm md:text-base text-ash-200">
              <span class="meta-strip text-cobalt-400 mt-1">{`0${i + 1}`}</span>
              <span class="text-pretty">{s}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    {/* Pivot — "We build the architecture" */}
    <div class="mt-20 md:mt-28 grid grid-cols-12 gap-6">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9 md:col-start-3 border-t border-cobalt-500/40 pt-10 md:pt-14">
        <div class="meta-strip text-cobalt-400 mb-5">Resolution</div>
        <h3 class="font-display text-display-lg tracking-tightest text-cobalt-500 text-balance">
          We build the architecture.
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-ash-300 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed text-pretty">
          We don&rsquo;t write theoretical whitepapers or sell you bloated SaaS subscriptions.
          We get our hands dirty in the internal mechanics of your business, integrating the
          world&rsquo;s most powerful platforms to build robust, automated systems that run
          flawlessly in the background.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
